insect.coverage.analysis
Class Profiling

java.lang.Object
  insect.coverage.analysis.Analysis
      insect.coverage.analysis.Profiling
public class Profiling
extends Analysis

Provides profile information regarding executions of an instrumented program.
Note: For methods requiring a method signature as an argument, the method signature must be in the following format:
.
where is the fully qualified name of the class of the method, is simply the name of the method, and is as described in the Java Virtual Machine Specification at:
http://java.sun.com/docs/books/vmspec/2nd-edition/html/ClassFile.doc.html#7035

Author:
Anil Chawla

timesStatementExecuted

public long timesStatementExecuted(java.lang.String className,
                                   int srcLine)
Determines the total number of times the specified statement was executed across all executions. Use timesStatemedExecuted(String, String, int) for efficiency if the containing method is known.

Parameters:
className - fully qualified name of class.
srcLine - source line number.
Returns:
number of times, or -1 on error.
